Question Q1 (A) Any 5

a) tracert / traceroute-
It shows the path (route) taken by packets from source to destination and displays each hop (router).

b) ip addr vs ifconfig-
ip addr: Modern command, more powerful (Linux recommended)
ifconfig: Older command, limited features

c) nslookup-
Used to query DNS to find IP address of a domain name.

d) Dynamic IP (DHCP)-
Advantages:-
Automatic IP assignment
Easy network management
Disadvantages:-
IP may change
Less control/security

f) Switch function-
A switch connects devices in a LAN and forwards data using MAC addresses.

g) Network topology-
It is the layout/structure of a network (e.g., star, bus).
Applications: LAN design, network planning, troubleshooting


Q2 (B) Bus Topology (C Program)

#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int n;
    printf("Enter number of nodes: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);
    printf("\nBus Topology Representation:\n");
    for(int i=1; i<=n; i++) {
        printf("[PC%d]", i);
        if(i != n)
            printf(" -- ");
    }
    printf("\n(All nodes connected to single backbone cable)\n");
    return 0;
}





















